<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881012-0114 </DOCNO><HL> Toronto Futures Exchange </HL><SO> </SO><CO> CANDA </CO><IN> CMD SCR NDX </IN><G> CFT </G><DATELINE> TORONTO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Toronto Futures Exchange said the U.S. Commodity Futures Trading Commission has issued a &quot;no-action&quot; letter to the exchange regarding the Toronto 35 Index futures contract, which &quot;effectively means&quot; the contract can be lawfully offered and sold in the U.S. to U.S. investors.    The exchange said the contract is a vehicle for foreign investors and international fund managers to gain or hedge exposure in the Canadian equity market. Exposure to the U.S. market will help the contract reach its full potential, it said. </TEXT></DOC>